tags.description: Rocky Bluff Campground offers solitude in a wooded setting and is located 3 miles south of Hot Springs. The 1.2 mile Spring Creek Nature Trail circles the campground and meanders beside the creek, an excellent trout stream. Open Memorial Day-Labor Day.
tags.name: Rocky Bluff Campground

tags.description: Most of the widely-spaced campsites have streamside views and are well screened with native vegetation. While visiting, try your hand at fishing for trout in Paint Creek (seasonally stocked).
tags.name: Paint Creek Campground

tags.description: The small campground has eight widely-spaced campsites. Picnic facilities for small and large groups include a covered pavilion and three areas with clustered tables and grills.
tags.name: Houston Valley Campground

tags.description: This campground is located near the top of Round Mountain in Cocke County. Situated at 3,100 feet, it is one of the highest-elevation campgrounds in Cherokee National Forest.
tags.name: Round Mountain Campground

tags.name: Lake Powhatan Campground
